<exercisegroup cols="2">
<title>Recognizing echelon forms</title>

<introduction><p>
	For each matrix,
	decide whether it is in <term><xref ref="definition-row-red-ref" text="title" /></term> (REF).
	For those that are,
	decide whether it is in <term><xref ref="definition-row-red-rref" text="title" /></term> (RREF).
</p></introduction>

<exercise>
	<statement><p><m>\displaystyle
		\begin{amatrix}{rrrrr}
			1 \amp 0 \amp -9 \amp 0 \amp -5 \\
			0 \amp 1 \amp  0 \amp 5 \amp -9 \\
			0 \amp 0 \amp  1 \amp 0 \amp  7 \\
			0 \amp 0 \amp  0 \amp 1 \amp  5
		\end{amatrix}
	</m></p></statement>
	<answer><p>
		This matrix is in REF but not RREF because there are columns
		that contain both a leading one and another non-zero entry.
	</p></answer>
</exercise>

<exercise>
	<statement><p><m>\displaystyle
		\begin{amatrix}{rrr}
			1 \amp 0 \amp   0 \\
			0 \amp 2 \amp   0 \\
			0 \amp 0 \amp  -1 \\
		\end{amatrix}
	</m></p></statement>
	<answer><p>
		This matrix is not in REF because the first non-zero entry
		in each of the second and third rows is not one.
	</p></answer>
</exercise>

<exercise>
	<statement><p><m>\displaystyle
		\begin{amatrix}{rrrr}
			1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp  4 \\
			0 \amp 1 \amp 0 \amp  0 \\
			0 \amp 0 \amp 1 \amp -2 \\
			0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp  0
		\end{amatrix}
	</m></p></statement>
	<answer><p> This matrix is in RREF. </p></answer>
</exercise>

<exercise>
	<statement><p><m>\displaystyle
		\begin{amatrix}{rrrr}
			1 \amp 0 \amp 3 \amp 0 \\
			0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \\
			0 \amp 1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \\
			0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 1 \\
		\end{amatrix}
	</m></p></statement>
	<answer><p> This matrix is in not in REF because is a zero row that appears above some of the non-zero rows. </p></answer>
</exercise>

<exercise>
	<statement><p><m>\displaystyle
		\begin{amatrix}{rrr}
			1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \\
			1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \\
			0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \\
		\end{amatrix}
	</m></p></statement>
	<answer><p>
		This matrix is not in REF because the leading one in the second row
		does not appear to the right of the leading one in the first column.
	</p></answer>
</exercise>

<exercise>
	<statement><p><m>\displaystyle
		\begin{amatrix}{rrrr}
			0 \amp 1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \\
			0 \amp 0 \amp 1 \amp 0 \\
			0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 1 \\
		\end{amatrix}
	</m></p></statement>
	<answer><p> This matrix is in RREF. </p></answer>
</exercise>

</exercisegroup>
